  <!--Elite Lanius Spawning Stuff-->


  <textList name="TEXT_ABC_ELITELANIUS">
    <text>As your ship exits its jump, you're stared down by the shimmering hull of a Lanius vessel. For such metal hungry creatures you're surprised they don't have more holes on their ships. Though, it does leaves you more to salvage if you blow the whole thing to bits. Before you can ponder the matter further, your ship detects the flicker of their weapons and you get ready for combat.</text>
    <text>As your codex said, in-front of you lies an obviously elite Lanius. You can tell by the... paint job? Well, you suppose it's nice that they're color coordinated at least. It lets you tell whose ship you raid for parts and whose ship you leave as a few spinning pieces of scrap in the vacuum. Try to avoid tha latter, or there might not be anything left for you to loot.</text>
    <text>As it always does, your codex gave you a rather accurate lead on your hunt. Now granted, this one is a bit above your average fare. That cargo hold is likely to hold something far more valuable than simply scrap, assuming you don't burn it, melt it, shred it, laser it, ion it, or any of the other myriad ways you could turn it into nothing but slag.</text>
    <text>As you exit your jump you’re greeted with the familiar sound of engines firing, a rather sharp looking ship turning to greet you. Sharp in the way it has many blades, honestly it’s pretty ugly, you care more about what’s in the cargo hold though. As the ship approaches you prepare for battle.</text>
  </textList>
