  <!--Normal Obelisk Spawning Stuff-->


  <textList name="TEXT_ABC_OBELISK">
    <text>As your ship exits its jump, your sensors pick up on a few of the Obelisk communication waves. A series of panicked murmurs are audible in the background, before they seem to direct a few words at you. "Oh, by the Queen's own chassis, it's these skin sacks again!" Communications cut off, and the ship engages yours. It would be in your best interest to keep the ship intact if you want whatever's onboard.</text>
    <text>Your ship's engines cool, and you're faced with the boxy design of an Obelisk ship. What is with them and rectangles? Their guns are like boxes, their ships are a bunch of mashed together boxes, and they ARE boxes. Well, you probably should try not to crack open this box unless you want to ruin their loot. You detect their weapons heating up, and prepare to engage.</text>
    <text>As you jump into the system, you receive a stream of garbled symbols and beeps from the Obelisk ship. While your translator may be on the fritz, the meaning isn’t lost on you when their weapons lock onto your hull! Maybe if you leave their ship intact, you'll be able to make this worth your time.</text>
    <text>Your codex is infallible as ever, even for such rare creatures as this they are exactly where it says they are. Of course, it seems they aren’t surprised to see you judging by the readied weapons. You consider communicating for half a second, just to taunt them, but the rapidly rising power signatures in their ship makes you scramble for combat.</text>
    <text>While they aren't as dangerous or as rare as a royal, a regular Obelisk ship is rather big game. Though what you care about more are the big guns contained inside, which you should try not to reduce into some scrap only fit for an augmented to eat. Though they are rather intent on destroying you it seems, considering you can spot the green glow forming in their weapons.</text>
  </textList>
