  <!--Royal Obelisk Spawning Stuff-->


  <textList name="TEXT_ABC_ROYALOBELISK">
    <text>You don’t even give your engines a chance to properly tune as you drop out of lightspeed, tearing through space in the direction your computer tells you the Royal is located in. The moment your ship detects another vessel, you lock on and charge weapons, and as you rip into weapons range you can see the white hull amidst a sea of darkness. It’s about time you taught these glorified boxes with a god complex who’s really supreme around here, and their decadent civilization is long past its prime. Mulch their ‘superior forms’ and their technology will fall right into your lap. </text>
    <text>Your codex’s coordinates led to this place, and it proves ever accurate; you spot the glowing pink of an Obelisk Royal and notice that they seem to have opened communications. "Ugh, more mortals. You have a serious death wish don't you?" You throw your weapons online, as they do the same.</text>
    <text>As you drop out of lightspeed, your computer begins its work. However, it appears you won’t need its help as you almost plough straight into a geometric vessel with a bright white hull. Looks like these floating rocks decided to drop anchor on top of the beacon, an arrogant display that you are going to remedy quickly. You stare into the pink glow of the vessel as you plot their demise, weapons already charging up. Send these boxes back to the hell they crawled out of, and their ’superior technology’ is yours.</text>
    <text>You barely are able to recalibrate your sensors to realspace when you’re blindsided by the Royal nearby! While the Royal ego is larger than a supergiant star, it takes a special kind of arrogance to leave the safety of their homeworlds. Now would be the best time to put them in your proper place, and claim their prized tech for yourself. Wipe the decks clean of their foul geometry, and the loot will be easy pickings.</text>
