  <!--Flavor text list for upgrading hive mantis to free mantis-->
  <textList name="TEXT_TWISTED_MANTIS_UPGRADE_MANTIS_TO_FREE_MANTIS">
    <text>Your Mantis is initially hostile towards the idea of consuming such a strange beverage, but eventually they relent and take a sip of the Queen's Tea. Within moments, you can see their once battle-hardened expression fade into a carefree smile.</text>
    <text>You sit your Mantis down and attempt to explain proper teatime etiquette to them. When that fails, you tell them that teatime was an Old Earth warrior's tradition, fit for only the bravest and most brutal. You're barely halfway through your improvised explanation when your Mantis grabs the tea and begins chugging vigorously. You step back, knowing better than to get in between a Mantis and their prey.</text>
    <text>You enter the dining hall to find that your Mantis has spilled their tea for the sixth time in the past hour. The problem is quickly solved once you acquire a sippie cup for them, and the tea immediately begins to take effect.</text>
    <text>Your Mantis is surprisingly willing to partake in the Queen's Tea! You're somewhat confused, until they ask how you managed to obtain tea from Leikonpliiinakra herself. You do your best to put on a straight face and give a convincing reply.</text>
  </textList>

  <!--Flavor text list for upgrading hive mantis to suzerain-->
  <textList name="TEXT_TWISTED_MANTIS_UPGRADE_MANTIS_TO_SUZERAIN">
    <text>You invite your Mantis to enjoy some of the Queen's Tea alongside you before the next jump. As they take a sip, their eyes widen at once. "Captain, what is being put in beverages? It very strong, and making for good drinkings!" You ask them how they feel, and they respond by sawing the table clean in half in mere moments! "I feeling very strong like Mantis warrior, Captain! Am ready to do the killings!"</text>
    <text>Your Mantis carefully observes the small teacup in front of them with a curious expression. "This is for drinkings, yes?" You nod, and gesture for them to go ahead and have some. They sip the tea hesitantly at first, then greedily gulp the rest of it down. You shudder to imagine what the Queen would say about her beloved tea being consumed in such an unruly manner.</text>
    <text>You find your Mantis practicing a strange haka in their quarters. They barely pause for a moment to accept the tea from you, and immediately return to their motions after guzzling it down. They say nothing else, but you take note of the newly-found vigor in their movements.</text>
    <text>Your Mantis is eating a dish that you don't recognize in the cafeteria. You carefully replace their drink with the Queen's Tea when they aren't looking, and leave before they notice you. Later, you get an automated alert from the ship's training center, informing you that one of your crew has completed all of the standard combat simulations without flaw. You put in a request for some more advanced training protocols.</text>
  </textList>

  <!--Flavor text list for upgrading suzerain to bishop-->
  <textList name="TEXT_TWISTED_MANTIS_UPGRADE_SUZERAIN_TO_BISHOP">
    <text>You approach your Suzerain from behind with a carefully prepared beverage. In a blur, they whirl around and knock you to the ground by reflex, hooking the teacup in a claw deftly before it spills. "Should not be surpisings me like this, Captain! Thankings for tea, howevers!" You smile hesitantly, making a note to not approach them unseen again. </text>
    <text>Your Suzerain is cleaning their armor, scrubbing out some bloodstains with their acidic spit. You ask them if they've ever wanted to try white armor instead as you present the tea to them "Hmm, have always been wanting to be Bishop! White will be harder cleanings, though..."</text>
    <text>You watch as your Suzerain races the other crew around the ship. You stop them for a moment, and ask if they would like a refreshment. They gulp down the tea rapidly, and then continue sprinting. You barely blink before they're coming around the ship again, the scent of trailing close behind.</text>
    <text>Your Suzerain is slicing away at a practice dummy in the training center. They pause to accept the tea, and then resume their attack. As you turn to leave, you whirl back around when you hear a tearing sound, and see the dummy in pieces on the floor! "Might be needing replacings, Captain..."</text>
  </textList>

  <!--Flavor text list for upgrading free mantis to hive mantis-->
  <textList name="TEXT_TWISTED_MANTIS_UPGRADE_FREE_MANTIS_TO_MANTIS">
    <text>Your Free Mantis is greedily inhaling some pheromones in their quarters. They gaze at you in awe as you approach with the Queen's Tea, and ask if they can have some. As they drink, their expression changes, and they knock their phermones to the ground in disgust. "What was I thinkings, Captain? Natural pheromones much betters!"</text>
    <text>Your Free Mantis is bragging to the others about "How Captain is think favorite of them," and they grin triumphantly as you approach with your gift. Their idolization of you is tiresome at times, but you're still going to miss it a little...</text>
    <text>You find your Free Mantis "playing chess" in the dining hall. They're concentrating hard, and they turn to you to ask "Captain, which one is pawn again?" You sigh, and ask if they want a break to have some tea. They drink up, and thank you "Brain is much more cleared, Captain!" They confidently move their knight forward by a space, and you don't bother to correct them.</text>
    <text>To your surpise, you find your Free Mantis trying to make tea on their own! As you take in the scene, it's clear they don't have any idea what they're doing. They've tried using pheromones instead of water, and the contents of the tea bag are all over the floor. You offer to make the tea yourself, and they gratefully accept. "You are biggest smartest, Captain!"</text>
  </textList>

  <!--Flavor text list for upgrading free mantis to warlord-->
  <textList name="TEXT_TWISTED_MANTIS_UPGRADE_FREE_MANTIS_TO_WARLORD">
    <text>Your Free Mantis is brewing up some pheromones in their quarters. You ask them if they'd like something to drink, and present the Queen's Tea. They take it, and they pour the whole thing in with their pheromone mixture! Later, you notice the growths of their head plate have become much more prominent. Guess you can't argue with results...</text>
    <text>You walk around the ship, and find your Free Mantis debating over what kind of music is the best. They stop for a moment to drink the tea that you've brought them, and continue their debate with new vigor. You're almost certain that none of these genres actually exist, but you're not going to argue with a freshly-made Warlord.</text>
    <text>Your Free Mantis has just finished taking some of their pheromones, and is gazing up at the ceiling sleepily. When they go to drink the Queen's Tea, nearly half of it dribbles down their face. Their focus sharpens quickly, and they rise up, quickly moving to make more pheromones. "Am suddenly wanting more, Captain! Want sharings?" You respectfully decline, and leave before the fumes get to you.</text>
    <text>As you take stock of the ship's resources, you notice an unusally large surplus of pheromones in the cargo. You question your Free Mantis about this over a cup of tea, but you're unable to get a coherent response out of them. The issue resolves itself in a few hours, as they rapidly burn through their supply.</text>
  </textList>

  <!--Flavor text list for upgrading warlord to crackerjack-->
  <textList name="TEXT_TWISTED_MANTIS_UPGRADE_WARLORD_TO_CRACKERJACK">
    <text>You turn to your Free Mantis Warlord and offer them the Queen's Tea. They accept the now-familiar challenge with gusto, draining the whole pot in seconds! "Queen herself would be proud, Captain!" You assure them that Leikonpliiinakra would be very impressed, and they look at you in confusion. "Why would Leikonpliiinakra be caring of tea? Am talking about REAL Queen!"</text>
    <text>Your Free Mantis Warlord drinks the tea in front of you with vigor. You avert your eyes for a moment as they guzzle the tea with a complete lack of poise or etiquette. You look back at them once they're finished, and are surpised by their new outfit! You're not sure where they got a bearskin hat so quickly, but you know better than to ask questions... </text>
    <text>Your Free Mantis Warlord is exchanging jokes with the rest of the crew, bursting into laughter before anybody can even get to the punchline. You wait for them to catch their breath, and present the Queen's Tea to them. Later, you watch as the crew tries for hours to make them laugh as they stand stoically in front of their quarters.</text>
    <text>You hold your breath as you enter your Warlord's quarters, and your eyes burn as their mixture of pheromones bubbles furiously. You wave to get their attention, and quickly hand the tea to them before you pass out from the fumes. A few hours later, you walk by their doorway and are surprised by a rather pleasant smell. Are they making... Tea?</text>
  </textList>

