  <textList name="TEXT_CREW_TALK_FORGEMASTER" ignoreUnique="true">
    <text>Alastair tells you stories about some of the strangest weapons he has ever made.</text>
    <text>Alastair tells you stories about some of the strongest weapons he has ever made.</text>
    <text>Alastair tells you stories about some of the weakest weapons he has ever made.</text>
    <text>Alastair greets you politely in the hall, but has a lot on his mind.</text>
    <text>Alastair greets you politely in the cafeteria, and pats the seat next to you. The man eats even more than his Plated do!</text>
    <text>Alastair inquires if you would be interested in taking up smithing, you politely decline.</text>
    <text>You are surprised to see that Alastair does not ask your crew to join the ranks of the Plated.</text>
    <text>"Lad, you ever stop and count all the stars? It's a great way to pass the time." Alastair says to you in passing.</text>
    <text>As you pass the cafeteria, you overhear Alastair laughing and sharing jolly stories with your crew.</text>
    <text>Alastair sends you a list of ways to improve your vessel's performance via your terminal. The workload this would require is immense, and you unfortunately have to decline utilizing the list.</text>
    <text>Alastair tells you about his collection of tiny colored rocks he has collected from different planets: "They simply evoke joy, Lad." He explains, grinning ear to ear.</text>
    <text>Alastair asks you what you think of the Theocracy. After you give your answer, he responds. "Interesting, well I won't think less of you regardless of your opinion, but good to know you aren't a devout follower or ally of them."</text>
    <text>You ask about Alastair's supported side, is he aligned with the Outcasts or the Theocracy? "Lad, I care little for support of either side's perspective. I simply take under my wing any who wish to improve their craft, instead of their governing body. That goes for you and your crew as well!"</text>
