  <textList name="TEXT_CREW_TALK_REMINGTON" ignoreUnique="true">
    <text>Remington knocks on your door. When you open it he nearly knocks you over from shoving a piece of paper so hard in your face. It is a blueprint for what appears to be a top-secret Federation android project, titled "Genesis". Remington asks you if the "robot" in the picture is single or not. You're speechless.</text>
    <text>You find a slip a paper under your door, it is from Remington. It reads: "Hello Captain, hacked your terminal and saw your browsing history. Is 'meatspin' some sort of human martial art lost to time? Please teach me the technique when you have some free time!". You immediately throw the note in the airlock and space it.</text>
    <text>You find Remington asking around for help with his crossword, as it currently has him stumped. Nobody else has any good answers for him.</text>
    <text>You knock on Remington's door and he allows you to enter. Inside he is building a gigantic jigsaw puzzle, almost as large as the room itself. He offers that you join him, you explain by the time you finish it the rebels will have overtaken Node 17, celebrated, and had grandkids.</text>
    <text>You receive a message on an encrypted channel from Admiral Tully himself. He gets straight to the point: "Listen to me, the Federation's entire database keeps getting replaced with a fictional story called 'Catboy Tully's adventures :3'. Thank god the one who does it puts our database back up an hour later. We have traced these database changes back to a terminal belonging to an individual named 'Mossberg' that is aboard your vessel. Son, is this a joke to you? Get your crew in line or I'll do it myself." He hangs up on you before you can answer. </text>
    <text>You find Remington in the cafeteria "singing" via beeps. His song is surprisingly catchy and a few of the other crew members are humming along or snapping their fingers, if they have any.</text>
    <text>You find a drawing on your door. Remington drew a crude drawing of you, your crew, and him in a group pose. It has a single word written on the back of the drawing: "Friend".</text>
    <text>Remington asks you if there is a way to seperate all Engis from the Harmony without killing them. You don't have any satisfactory answers for him, he seems disappointed.</text>
    <text>You ask Remington how he feels about his brother Mossberg. "I would take a bullet for my brother, then whatever nanomachines left on my person would take twelve more. Any other questions, Captain?"</text>
    <text>You find Remington trying to paint a superhero motif on one of your ship's consoles, presumably from one of his comics. You sterly tell him to cease painting on delicate equipment.</text>
  </textList>

